2024巴黎奧運7月26日至8月11日於法國巴黎舉行，為表達對台灣選手之支持，總統賴清德與副總統蕭美琴昨（29）日晚間分別以錄影方式為巴黎奧運台灣代表團選手加油，並於FB、IG、YouTube等社群媒體上號召國人一起為台灣英雄應援。
 賴清德、蕭美琴指出，巴黎奧運代表團選手們經過努力不懈的訓練，如今終於站上賽場發光發熱，跟各國運動員競技切磋。
  賴清德認為，每一位出征奧運的選手都非常不簡單，希望大家都能盡情發揮、享受比賽，拿出最好的表現。蕭美琴則感謝選手們帶來每一刻振奮人心的感動，相信都會成為台灣繼續無畏前進的力量。
  賴清德與蕭美琴強調，他們與全體國人都會做大家最強後盾，跨越距離和時差，為選手們加油應援、鼓掌歡呼，並肯定所有代表團選手都是台灣英雄，「台灣因你們而驕傲、因你們而耀眼」、「巴黎奧運 Taiwan all win！不必客氣，全力以赴！加油！」。
  賴清德在影片中提到，這是小戴、李洋在奧運的最後一舞，雖然有些不捨，但他非常期待看到他們的精采表現；他也對走過傷勢低潮的郭婞淳說，這是她第四次挑戰奧運，謝謝她沒有放棄，也期待看她繼續突破自我，綻放最自信的笑容。
  賴清德向第六次征戰奧運的莊智淵說，「想當年你第一次參加奧運，才23歲，轉眼已經成為台灣桌球教父」。
  此外，賴清德在影片中特別別上珍奶別針、擺上具有台味的「茄芷袋」鑰匙圈。包括珍奶別針、「茄芷袋」鑰匙圈，都是此次為巴黎奧運代表團特別設計的紀念小物，讓選手能夠帶去巴黎分送給其他國家的奧運好手，羽球天后戴資穎日前也在IG上大讚「今年徽章設計超可愛」。

上市不久的 Galaxy Watch Ultra 是 Samsung 現時市場定位最高，同時亦是定價最高的智能手錶，不過近日就傳出錶身漆面剝落的問題。用戶 bimmerb0ii 日前在 Reddit 討論區發帖分享自身經歷，表示他的灰色 Galaxy Watch Ultra 使用短短數日，錶底的漆面就出現剝落情況。
 bimmerb0ii 的 Galaxy Watch Ultra 是與 Galaxy Z Fold6 一同訂購，他選擇了灰色的版本。該名用戶表示自己對新錶愛護有加，甚至連睡覺時都會佩戴，但就沒有戴著它前往健身房。他佩戴短短數天後發現，錶底左下方的螺絲旁邊出現漆面剝落，對於漆面短時間內迅速剝落，他大感不解。有外國媒體指似乎只有灰色的版本才會出現問題，因為 Galaxy Watch Ultra 白色和銀色款式的漆面主要集中在錶圈和錶側部分。
  bimmerb0ii 透露自己聯繫的 Samsung 客戶服務建議他前往授權服務中心，但他到達後才得知服務中心並沒有 Galaxy Watch Ultra 的替換零件。他之後被告知可致電 Samsung 要求更換，結果在經歷約 30 分鐘等待後，最終客服人員提出賠償 22 美元讓他保留有問題的手錶。這名用戶對安排並不滿意，現在要求 Samsung 作出更換，但因為手錶在購買 Galaxy Z Fold6 時以優惠價購入，但現在優惠期已過，令整個過程變得異常複雜。

狄鶯和 孫鵬 的獨子孫安佐近期風波不斷，先前更因為和同行友人持「瓦斯火槍」以及家中存有武器而引發話題，沒想到今（16日）凌晨在直播中表示要募款70萬飛去烏克蘭打戰，對於兒子的行為，狄鶯一直沒正面回應，消息傳出後她臉書首度發聲。
 孫安佐對於槍械十分感興趣，直播中透露要設立網站，並且募資70萬元買裝備並聲稱要到烏克蘭打戰，對於兒子的行為，狄鶯先是冷笑兩聲，無奈回應：「你們自己問他吧。」，對於兒子想要參軍的想法笑而不答。

 Stephanie十八歲的甜點夢如今築夢踏實.。壹拾捌甜點室 提供
  Stephanie出生餐飲家庭，父母生意做得很不錯，追尋甜點夢之前，在家裡很少吃苦，但就特別愛吃甜點，所以綽號叫「法式甜點小公主」。 「因為我從小就愛吃法式甜點，18歲那一年，Stephanie就決定要當法式甜點師傅，但是學業和家庭的羈絆，讓她直到2018年才正式邁開大步，前進日本東京的法國藍帶學院學習法式甜點廚藝。
  她吸取來自世界各國的美食養分與創意，學成回到台灣以後，在台北信義區開了一家法式甜點店，自己擔任主廚CHEF，法文店名叫DIX-HUIT PÂTISSERIE，中文意思就是壹拾捌甜點室，她就用這家甜點店來回應自己的投入，宣告她的甜點夢終於築夢踏實。
  「我們堅持用最好的原料，做出最美味的甜點，希望帶給客人「家」的幸福感。」這是Stephanie做甜點的自我期許，也是她經過東京的法國藍帶學院廚藝殿堂洗禮之後，承襲藍帶職人精神與日本職人專注堅持的核心思維，她希望能提供顧客無法抗拒又滿足的甜點誘惑，共享視覺味覺的美感與幸福滋味。
  Stephanie因為家人愛吃芋泥蛋糕研發的厚芋泥巴斯克-A(大甲芋泥與西班牙乳酪蛋糕的完美結合）壹拾捌甜點室 提供
  因為深信甜點是人體快樂的荷爾蒙與幸福的因子，能夠傳遞家的幸福感，所以，Stephanie把家的意念，變成了壹拾捌甜點室的識別標誌，她的甜點店的LOGO就是一個家，走入店裡的客人，就是她的家人。
  Stephanie的法式中秋月餅-B（同一種月餅台灣人老外都喜歡）壹拾捌甜點室 提供
  為了招待所有的顧客「家人」，Stephanie採用法式、日式完美調和的純手工甜點製作工法，除了嚴選原料食材之外，她特別加入台灣在地的好食材，讓客人可以感受到家的溫暖、出國的喜悅與低調的奢華感。Stephanie認為：甜點是啟動快樂荷爾蒙的催化劑，也是傳遞家庭溫暖的幸福因子，想吃美味道地的法式甜點、感受愛與家的溫暖，到壹拾捌甜點室（DIX-HUIT PÂTISSERIE）就對了！

The SEA tech scene is a unique, vibrant, and rapidly advancing region with its own strengths and opportunities
 Global capital markets have acknowledged the reality of a shift in economic relevance from West to East. The G7 nations now represent only 44 per cent of global GDP, down from 67 per cent in 1994, while the other 13 G20 countries, including India, China, Brazil, and Saudi Arabia, have increased their share from 15 per cent to 25 per cent over the same period.
  Despite these realities, investor perceptions and rhetoric have not fully caught up. Recent discussions in various regional and global forums have highlighted misconceptions and inconsistencies about the fast-growing markets, including the Southeast Asian (SEA) markets.
  In these discussions, fast-growing markets are often painted as “developing” or akin to the “Wild West” (as one industry expert expressed to me), suggesting an inherent need to “catch up” with the West. Even opening the July 2024 World Economic Outlook by the IMF classifies countries still as advanced economies (pretty much the G-7) and emerging and developing economies, the rest.
  However, this couldn't be further from reality.
  Debunking misconceptions: A look at technological leadership
  China's meteoric rise in digital technology, AI, and quantum computing serves as a testament to the potential within what some call “emerging and developing” markets. Similarly, SEA's technology platforms in proptech, e-commerce, logistics, and other sectors often surpass or leapfrog their Western counterparts, demonstrating advanced technological integration and innovative approaches. Platforms like super apps, which combine multiple services into a single application, showcase SEA's ability to leapfrog traditional tech development stages.
  Even in simple life situations like applying for a new passport or lodging a tax return, the so-called “emerging and developing markets” outshine the so-called ‘advanced economies'. It takes one hour to get a new passport in Malaysia and 4-6 weeks in Australia or Germany.
  The same is true for internet speed, banking services and other necessities of modern daily life.
  Valuation and growth: A comparative analysis
  Sadly, due to the old rhetoric, valuation metrics still favour the West (even if declining or showing lower growth or a lower degree of technology adoption). Comparing investments in SEA with their Western counterparts shows that SEA players are still significantly discounted on a like-for-like basis despite high growth, high margins and other key business metrics in their favour.
  Also Read: How Web3 will revolutionise borderless banking in Southeast Asia
  While Western economies generally have a higher GDP per capita (which is a historic rather than future-looking indicator), SEA markets not only show significant growth but also comparable and often superior metrics in several tech-related areas:
  Internet penetration : Southeast Asia boasts high internet usage. For instance, Malaysia had 33.59 million internet users at the start of 2024, representing an internet penetration rate of 97.4 per cent (DataReportal: Global Digital Insights).
  Social media usage: Malaysia had 28.68 million social media users in January 2024, equating to 83.1 per cent of the total population (DataReportal: Global Digital Insights). The region leads in integrating social media with eCommerce, creating dynamic digital ecosystems that surpass many Western models.
  Mobile connectivity: In early 2024, Malaysia had 44.55 million active cellular mobile connections, equivalent to 129.2 per cent of the total population (DataReportal: Global Digital Insights).
  According to the latest DataReportal report, Southeast Asia continues to see impressive growth in digital behaviours and adoption. The region is home to some of the most engaged internet users which is critical for the adoption of new technologies thus explaining the meteoritic rise of some tech companies, with high levels of social media and mobile internet usage. The question remains: why are companies from these markets still being discounted on global markets?
  The illusion of copy-and-paste strategies
  A crucial lesson from the SEA market is the failure of a one-size-fits-all approach. Global tech giants have failed in Southeast Asia when they applied a copy-and-paste approach without understanding local market nuances. Uber's defeat in China and Southeast Asia illustrates this well. A successful strategy often involves a common data structure and a customised front end to meet local and regional demands.
  Embracing a new paradigm
  It's time to put “colonial-era” models and outmoded notions aside. Every sector of a nation's economy and every business operating in it ought to be assessed according to its own strengths, competitive landscape, and core values. Recognising emerging markets' distinct prospects and technological breakthroughs is crucial for investors and stakeholders to avoid losing out on substantial growth potential, especially in the tech sector.
  Also Read: A new breed of fintech payment is here to slay the game
  Rethinking labels: Emerging vs established
  The terms “emerging” and “established” or “developing” and “developed” are increasingly outdated. Western countries risk complacency by resting on the laurels of being deemed “established,” which can lead to economic decline, as seen in areas of innovation in Germany and the UK.
  Ignoring the rapid advancements and large user bases in regions like SEA is a strategic misstep for investors. With more than half of the world's internet users residing in Asia, including 10 per cent in Southeast Asia alone, the potential for growth and innovation is immense.
  Final thoughts
  The SEA tech scene is not a frontier to be tamed or a market trying to catch up with the West. Instead, it is a unique, attractive, vibrant, innovative, and rapidly advancing region with its own strengths and opportunities.
  By shifting the narrative and recognising the unique characteristics and opportunities, as well as the leadership of certain Asian countries, including SEA, in the area of technology adoption, we can foster a more accurate and equitable understanding of global tech landscapes. Embracing this perspective will not only benefit investors but also drive innovation and growth across the globe.

  In questo video viene raccontata la normalità del quotidiano fino ad arrivare alla preparazione di un sogno da realizzare: “un giovane uomo che accoglie le responsabilità del lavoro e della famiglia, che lotta tutti i giorni per riuscire a guadagnare il suo spazio in un mondo fatto di sudore e rinunce. Questo mondo lo riconosciamo nei suoi occhi nella sua voglia di vincere e riuscire ad essere l'uomo e il campione di boxe che ha sempre immaginato”.
  Scritto e diretto da Manuela Kalì , con la partecipazione di Davide Argenti , attore in “Martedì e Venerdì” regia Fabrizio Moro “Il Permesso” regia Claudio Bonivento e Claudio Amendola, “Pasolini” regia di Abel Ferrara, “Baby” regia Andrea De Sica e Anna Negri, “Suburra 3” regia Arnaldo Catinari.
  Massimiliano Renzi , autore del brano, prodotto artisticamente da Federico Coderoni , racconta così il brano: “Ci arrendiamo al tempo che passa, conviviamo con scelte sbagliate, teniamo il conto di chi se ne va, di chi rimane e ci affolliamo la mente di domande – spiega la band romana formata: “ le risposte spesso cambiano e il tempo con noi. Vorremmo soluzioni, carezze, giustificazioni, ma non sappiamo a chi chiedere, non sappiamo a chi dare fiducia senza essere giudicati. Accusiamo il dolore in modo estremo, chiedendoci se un giorno ci restituirà quello che ci ha tolto e se ciò che rimarrà sarà qualcosa di bello da riuscire a raccontare”.
  I Rossonoha sono una band di Roma, cresciuti sotto i colpi melodici dei Beatles e della prima genesi elettronica. Tra studio, scrittura e la continua ricerca tra i vari club che proponevamo musica indipendente. Poi l'incontro con Flavio Ferri , produttore e cofondatore della famosa band Delta V. Inizia la collaborazione con Ferri che produce i brani del primo disco di Rossonoha. Partecipa con il brano “Solo per te” alle selezioni di Sanremo.
  Un progetto, un sound che varia dagli 80 ai 145 bpm senza lasciare il tempo di riflettere, un altro viaggio che viene presentato nei vari club. Esce il singolo “Sei” , presentato su Sky Arte , mentre TGCOM24 prosegue il viaggio presentando il singolo, “ Rumore” . Premiati alla kermesse Roma Videoclip – il cinema incontra la musica e al Concorso Laziowave , successivamente aprono il concerto dei Marlene Kuntz a Frosinone. Poco dopo esce la cover della celebre canzone del Maestro Franco Califano intitolata TAC . Rossonoha cambia rotta e decide di creare i nuovi brani sotto la produzione artistica di produttori tra la Gran Bretagna e la Germania . Nel frattempo, escono i singoli “Passo Le Notti”, che supera ogni aspettativa negli ascolti e “ Siamo Ancora Qui” , riflessione musicale sull'odio, sull'essere umano, sulla vita di chi fa fatica ad arrivare a fine mese.
  Nel 2021 e 2022, nel momento delle riaperture post pandemia, i Rossonoha vanno in Tour nelle periferie romane, tra i palazzi e i parchi delle realtà popolari per esserci, per ripartire insieme. I giornali della capitale evidenziano l'iniziativa. Finalisti ad Arezzo Wave nel 2022 . Dopo il brano, “Dall'altra parte della strada” , nel 2023 esce il singolo Post-it “avevamo bisogno di questo brano, era per noi urgente e così abbiamo voluto attaccare un post-it per ogni anno passato, per ogni momento vissuto, per ogni occasione mancata, per ogni battaglia persa”. A novembre 2023 esce il nuovo singolo “Animali Strani”, accompagnato dal videoclip GUARDA VIDEOCLIP , scritto e diretto da Manuela Kalì , con la partecipazione di Elisa Rocchetti , attrice in “A casa tutti bene” – 2a stagione, con la regia di Gabriele Muccino e “ Accattaroma” di Daniele Costantini
